rComments: Really chill and laid-back (sometimes a little bit too much). Need more TA's though.

I havent finished phya11 with him yet but so far hes really kind and helpful. Hes not condescending and is patient when explaining things. The textbook is necessary because his slides dont really go in depth. If you study and do his questions in the slide youll do well on the midterm (it was fair) good luck :)
Fair prof. doesn't try to trick you. not easy though - found the class challenging. ended up doing well.
Useless slides, lectures, and demos. Just followed the textbook and got an easy A+

Great prof who wants students to succeed. His lectures stay close to the textbook, which is good and bad. definitely do the practice problems since some were on the tests. participation is an easy 5%, so I went to lectures at least for that. approachable prof for questions, but I admit I only went to office hours once.
Not an easy class, but well-organized. Many of the questions on tests were done in lecture, so that's helpful. Was easy to get help during office hours.

I felt like his lectures didn't much reflect the questions we were assigned to do, as in he would often skip doing question demos if short in lecture time. That wasn't helpful as the examinations were more based on problem-solving than concept based.
